  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mechanical Technician",
  "description": "<p>ShaftRise Engineering & Services Pte Ltd is a service provider in marine and industrial repair and precision services. We are seeking a motivated individual to join us as a Mechanical Technician. This is a hands-on role where you will develop expertise in critical precision measurement and alignment techniques using advanced laser technologies. Under the guidance of senior technicians and surveyors, you will learn how to ensure that industrial equipment and structures meet precise dimensional specifications and operational requirements.<br /></p><h2>Responsibilities:</h2><ul><li>To support senior surveyors in performing dimensional control surveys, fit-up inspections, and as-built surveys on various structures and components (e.g., steel structures, modules, piping).</li><li>To use advanced laser alignment systems (e.g., Fluke, Pruftechnik, Easy Laser) for the precision alignment of rotating machinery (pumps, motors, engine, gearboxes, etc.).</li><li>To accurately collect, record, and process survey and alignment data using specialised software (e.g., CAD, 3D software).</li><li>To assist in preparing detailed reports, drawings, and documentation of survey and alignment results for client submission.</li><li>Responsible for handling, calibration, and maintenance of precision measuring equipment.</li><li>Strictly adhere to all safety protocols and procedures while working in industrial and marine environments.</li><li>Work closely with experienced engineers and construction teams to understand project requirements and provide effective support.</li></ul><h2>Qualifications:</h2><ul><li>Any related technical field is preferred.</li><li>Must have a strong willingness to learn, a keen eye for detail, and a problem-solving mindset.</li><li>Physically fit and able to perform fieldwork</li><li>Strong basic communication skills for accurate data recording and team interaction.</li></ul><p></p>",
